commentTextItems.html: fraction short outside off stump, batsman punches through covers, winning runs from Hogg!

commentPostTextItems.html: Australians have thrashed the Bangladesh with Cosgrove using his chance and smashing 74 runs off just 69 balls. Katich gave him good support and they have swept the series 3-0. Hogg was declared Man-of-Series for his 9 wickets and Cosgrove adjudged Man-of-Match in his debut match. Cheers and bye!

dismissalText.commentary: Mark Cosgrove b Abdur Razzak 74 (69b 7x4 2x6 94m) SR: 107.24

commentTextItems.html: length ball outside off stump, batsman moves forward and tries to heave it across, gets the inside edge onto the stumps
good length delivery, Cosgrove uses his feet and tries to loft, gets the top edge and ball goes high in the air but falls safe straight and wide of the long-off fielder
good length delivery, Cosgrove uses his feet and tries to work it away, gets on the pads
good line and length delivery, Katich keeps it out

stories.title: Nafees fined for dissent
stories.subTitle: Australia in Bangladesh 2005-06
stories.summary: Shahriar Nafees, the Bangladesh opener, has been fined 20% of his match fees for dissent during the third one-day international against Australia at Fatullah

stories.title: Cosgrove helps Australia complete rout
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v Australia, 3rd ODI, Fatullah,
stories.summary: Powered by a disciplined bowling performance which shot out Bangladesh for a disappointing 124, Australia chased down the meager target in style to complete a whitewash
